NumberFormat Class:->
-> various locations follow various styles to represent a java number.for example
double d = 123456.789;
India people => 1,23,456.789
US people => 123,456.789
Italy People => 123.456,789
-> we can use number format class to format a java number according to a particular locale.

-> number format class present in java.text package and it is a abstract class.
NumberFormat nf = new NumberFormat();
//invalid it is a abstract class we can't create object.
-> getting number format object for default locale.

-> number format class defines the following methods for this purpose.
public static NumberFormat getInstance();
public static NumberFormat getNumberInstance();
public static NumberFormat getCurrencyInstance();
public static NumberFormat getPercentageInstance();

Example:->
NumberFormat nf = NumberFormat.getInstance(); or NumberFormat nf = NumberFormat.getNumberInstance();
NumberFormat nf = NumberFormat.getCurrencyInstance();
NumberFormat nf = NumberFormat.getPercentageInstance();
